article.description:
Dirk Nowitzki scored 28 points, 10 during a
decisive 13-0 third-quarter run, as the Dallas Mavericks completed
a four-game season sweep of the Memphis Grizzlies with a 114-87
victory on Saturday night.
article.headline: Nowitzki scores 10 in Mavs' decisive 13-0 run

images.name: Nowitzki Dirk 030301 inline
images.caption: Dirk Nowitzki scored 10 of his 28 points during a 13-0 third-quarter Mavs run.

article.linkText: Mavs run away from Grizzlies with third-quarter spurt
article.story:
DALLAS (AP) -- Dirk Nowitzki, Eduardo Najera and Adrian Griffin energized the listless Dallas Mavericks. Nowitzki scored 28 points, 10 during a decisive 13-0 third-quarter run, while Najera and Griffin came off the bench to spark the Mavericks, who completed a four-game season sweep of the Memphis Grizzlies with a 114-87 victory on Saturday night. Griffin, activated off the injured list earlier in the day, went 8-for-8 for 17 points to help the Mavericks end a two-game losing streak. Najera, back in the rotation after sitting out a one-game suspension for bumping a game official earlier in the week, contributed 10 points and 10 rebounds. "Eddie and Adrian had big games,'' Mavericks guard Steve Nash said. "It was nice to have them back. No offense to that team, but this was a difficult game to get up for. It wasn't pretty for us starting out. But we did a good job finishing them off.'' The Mavericks missed Najera's rebounding and hustle on Thursday night when they were beaten in overtime by the Sacramento Kings, 126-124. "I was excited about coming back,'' Najera said. "Our intensity wasn't there early. I wanted to come in and try to pick up the intensity level. We were going through the motions, but in the second half we really turned it up.'' Nowitzki scored 13 points and went 3-of-4 from 3-point range during the third quarter when Dallas outscored Memphis 28-17. The Grizzlies were without starting center Lorenzen Wright, who returned to Memphis to be with his family following the death of his 11-month-old daughter, Sierra, on Saturday morning. "There were definitely a lot of heavy hearts here tonight,'' Memphis coach Hubie Brown said. "You never know how much energy it will drain from them. I thought we gave a gallant effort for 2½ quarters, but they went on that run and we didn't react well. We never recovered.'' Michael Finley had 11 points and 10 rebounds and the Mavericks got 53 points from their reserves. "We're going to need our bench down the stretch if we want to go all the way,'' Nowitzki said. "We're going to need 12 guys providing us with a great (effort). Then I think we're in good shape. It wasn't a pretty win, but we needed it after the Sacramento loss.'' Pau Gasol's 25 points and eight rebounds, and Stromile Swift's 16 points paced the Grizzlies, who've lost four of their last six and 11 straight to the Mavericks. Dallas took a 52-49 halftime lead behind 15 points from Nowitzki. Memphis opened the third quarter with a 10-0 run, taking advantage of eight straight Dallas misses to grab a 59-52 edge on a 14-footer by Gasol. But the Mavericks lifted their effort on the defensive end after coach Don Nelson criticized their lackluster play during a timeout. Nelson sent Najera and Nick Van Exel into the game, then brought in Griffin a few minutes later, and the Mavs went on a 13-0 spurt triggered by Nowitzki's 3-pointer. Nowitzki hit a 15-footer, then Najera converted a three-point play with 7:13 left in the third to give the Mavericks the lead for good at 60-59. Nowitzki drained another 3-pointer off a behind-the-back feed from Steve Nash, and made an 18-footer on the next possession to give Dallas a 65-59 edge. The Mavericks were up 80-66 going into the fourth quarter, and went on to lead by as many as 29 points over the final 12 minutes. "Nellie really got on us in that timeout,'' Nowitzki said. "(Najera) came in and really gave us a boost and that helped us pick up our energy level.'' Memphis missed 12 of its final 13 field goal attempts in the third quarter.

Game notes
The Grizzlies' road record fell to 4-25. ... Memphis players wore armbands with Wright's No. 42 in a show of support for their grieving teammate. ... Dallas' longest losing streak of the season is three games, which has happened twice. ... Mavericks C Raef LaFrentz picked up six fouls in 15 minutes and backup C Shawn Bradley was whistled for three fouls in seven minutes of the first half. ...The Mavericks are 23-1 when they hold their opponents to under 90 points.
